reviews.review_text:
Nice recording of my first show This version is a pretty nice AUD pull.  Since this was my first show (driving from Ithaca, NY to Chicago on an acid fueled road-trip), I have heard earlier tapes that circulated around at the time more than once. 

I was already "on the bus" when I came to the show, but since was my first time seeing the boys in person, you can imagine how transformative this show was for me.  I didn't have tickets, but we were lucky enough to get hooked up by a kind fellow in the parking lot who sold us his floor seats at face value. 

The second set stands out to me with an energetic, well played version of China >Rider that really got the crowd pumping.  I remember feeling chills as the crowd enthusiastically sang along with Jerry - "I wish I was a headlight on a northbound train!".  I've always had an affinity for Playin' and was thrilled to hear it live and to this day, those opening riffs define, for me, the GD "sound".

Thank you taper for taping and posting. Nice pull.
- The better set is the 1st, but both are pretty smokin' anyway. OK recording.
